   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1650_brd_ncd_r.jpg"/>

         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>الله اکبر</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div1" corresp="#orig_div1">
            <p>God is great</p>
         </div>

         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>زبده الاقران
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">پرسوتمداس</persName>
               چودری پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#jamli">جاملی</placeName>
                و
               <placeName ref="#hindola">هندوله</placeName>
                را انها آنکه
               <lb/> عرضه داشتی که درینولا مشتمل بر کیفیت بیجا شدن مردم مهاجن و
               <lb/>خوش باش قصبه
               <placeName ref="#sultanpur">سلطانپور</placeName>
                از بی سلوکی کروری آنجا قلمی نموده
               <lb/>ارسال داشته بود رسید و بر آن آگهی رفت و آنچه درین
               <lb/>ماده باستی بکروری آنجا نوشت نگاشته با این رقیمه نزد او
               <lb/>فرستاده آمد باید که باو برساند و باتفاق تسلی انجماعه نموده بمکان
               <lb/>اصلی آباد سازد و رعایا را مستمال ساخته در مزید زراعت و افزونی
               <lb/>کشتکار سرگرم دارد که باعث مجرای او در این خواهد بود زیاده تاکید
               <unclear>نرفت</unclear>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p>
               <lb/>Eminent among Contemporaries
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam Das</persName> chaudhri
                of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#jamli">Jamli</placeName>
                and <placeName ref="#hindola">Hindola</placeName>
                is informed that
               <lb/>the petition containing the account of the displacement of the well-off and 
               <lb/>important people of the town of <placeName ref="#sultanpur">Sultanpur</placeName> due to the ill behaviour of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_karori">karori</ref> of that place, that he had presently put in writing
               <lb/>and had been sent, was received. And on account of that the information arose and whatever
               <lb/>was written [in] a writing to the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_karori">karori</ref> regarding this matter of lowliness, it was sent to him
               <lb/>with this letter. It is essential that [this writing] shall be delivered to him, and that by causing the consolation of those people
               <lb/>he will make [them] settled in the original home. And having concilliated the peasants, he shall be occupied in the increase of cultivation
               <lb/>and the enlargement of husbandry for the cause of his progress will be in this. More compulsion <unclear>shall not arise</unclear>. 
            </p>
         </div>
         
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="right margin">
            <p>الله اکبر</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p>God is great</p>
         </div>
         
         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="right margin">
            <p>
               <lb/>اگر
               <gap></gap>
               راستی بوده
               <unclear>بصلح با یکدیگر الحاف</unclear>
               <lb/>کرده معامله پرگنه جاملی هندوله را از قرار
               <lb/>واقع خواهد پرداخت
               <unclear>نوری...</unclear>
                آنها است
               <lb/>و اگر
               <unclear>اجاه</unclear>
               خصومت بمیان اوردند
               <gap></gap>
               که نتیجه 
               <lb/>نیک نخواهد یافت زیاده چه نوشت
               <lb/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned><gap/>
                  <unclear>بنده</unclear>
                  <persName ref="#shahJahan">شاه جهان</persName>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div4" corresp="#orig_div4">
            <p>
               <lb/>If <gap/> is true, <unclear>compelling [them] to compromise with one another</unclear>
               <lb/>the affairs of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#jamli">Jamli</placeName> and <placeName ref="#hindola">Hindola</placeName> 
               <lb/>shall be as fixed.<gap/> is of them
               <lb/>And if they cause quarrels to arise, the result 
               <lb/>will not be good. What more was written.
              <lb/><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><gap/><unclear>servant of</unclear> <persName ref="#shahJahan">Shah Jahan</persName></mentioned></stamp><note>The document is undated, so a date has been ascribed
              using 1650, when <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam Das</persName> is known to become active, as an opening bound and the end of the reign of <persName ref="#shahJahan">Shah Jahan</persName>, i.e. 1659, as a closing bound on the basis of this seal.
              However, it is possible the seal continued to be used afterward. <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam Das</persName> was involved in a similar incident in 1669. See <ref type="bibl" target="#chatterjee2020">Chatterjee, Negotiating Mughal Law, p. 137</ref>.</note>
            </p>
         </div>
